Privacy Policy

Your privacy is important to us.

Unattach may read and update information on your Gmail account to your computer,
but does not distribute any of this information to any other location.

Unattach's use of information received from Google APIs will adhere to the Google
API Services User Data Policy, including the Limited Use requirements. See
http://tiny.cc/google-reqs-api-scopes for more info.

Unattach may send stack traces (in case of program failures) to our servers in
order to continually improve our service to you. We made every effort to ensure
that these stack traces don't contain any personal information.

Our website, https://unattach.app/, collects the standard analytics
information. We do not collect or share any personally-identifying information
publicly or with third-parties, except when required to by law.

Our website service stores information about purchases, upgrades and downloads.
This information is used only for internal purposes and is not shared with
third parties.

We may email you about your transactions (e.g. your purchase or upgrade). If
you are subscribed to product-related updates, we may email you occasionally
about such updates --- you can unsubscribe from these at any point.

We may use a third-party service for sending you emails, both transactional and
update-related. Your email address will not be shared with other third-parties
or for other purposes.

Our website may link to external site that are not operated by us. Please be
aware that we have no control over the content and practices of these sites,
and cannot accept responsibility or liability for their respective privacy
policies.

Your continued use of Unattach and/or its website will be regarded as acceptance
of our practices around privacy and personal information. If you have any
questions about how we handle user data and personal information, feel free to
contact us.

This policy is effective as of 3 Oct 2021.